        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Takilth SP</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Update on how to avoid the little Boulderling bastards.  FDing on these guys can be a pain because of their AoE.  Your best shot will be to run a quick distance away and FD as fast as possible before you get summoned.  I was actually thinking that this might be one instance where Shadowstepping might actually be useful - quick cast spell to get the necessary distance before you pop FD to get them off your back.  Also, the pet comes in useful here.  If you have him up, let them focus on him and then get some distance and FD.  Once they back off now you know where they are and can avoid them.  Recast pet and you're off and running again.  Remember not to waste time while they're taking down your pet - he won't last long.</P><P>I'm guessing these little fellows are soloable with the right spell lineup and persistance.  Since you can get them to focus on the pet the Vex/Bond/Shadowbond/Pact method might work.  I'll have to try next time I run into them.  Even though they don't give any/too much exp, they sure are fun to anhililate because of their annoyance factor :).</P><P>The secret is - if you run into them, already have a plan for what you're gonna do in place, or they'll tear you a new one.</P><P></P><P>Takilth Shadowpath<BR>aka Necrotart<BR>Iksar Warlock of the Final Shedding<BR>proud member of Shining Alliance<BR>Prexus</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Tenaiya</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Hmmm....no one seems to like soloing at the SD zone. I've always found it preferable to the ML zone myself (I think wanderers come too close for comfort). Brilliant fear kite pathing (they run more or less parallel to the wall) and absolutely no adds (occasional train yes, but no adds at all). Lots of space to maneuver about with root too. Most importantly, no rockfiends path near there on their own.</P><P>Set up to the left of the tunnel, should be a section of the wall that is smooth. There should be no boulders ahead (used to be able to set up right by the tunnel but the boulder in front of it now holds a rock trap). Run up to the ridge and pull mobs from there. They've now put 2 worm traps there too unfortunately. But there are some ways around them:<BR>1) if you have a pre-nerf CoS, use it. None of the triggered worms or rocks see through invis. Won't be able to use a pet though in the case, but makes for far far far safer pulling.<BR>2) if your particle settings (I think) are set to medium or higher, you will be able to see puffs of smoke showing you where they are.</P><P>There is usually a fairly steady stream of wanderers that head up to the ridge, only one or two will occasionally cross it. Failing that, there are usually skeles littered all over the place from failed kitings. I've always found pulling there to be rather easy for some weird reason.</P><P>I used to love hunting at the Temple. Then the key to VT was found and now random people keep running across the zone and training everything in sight, when it's actually fairly easy to get to the Temple without aggroing a single thing.</P><P>The two ruins that Takith mentioned that are to the right of ML: I just went there last week, and they've just put in a TON of traps around the one nearer ML. Not just slugs, but rocktraps too now.</P><P>Boulderlings are stupidly annoying. They're light blue, hit harder and faster than xakra, and all chain cast that ridiculous spell that xakras use too. I don't think it's really worthwhile soloing them.</P><P>This zone used to be fun, even after repeated nerfings. But this latest nerf of putting a trap under almost every rock has really taken away a lot of the fun in the zone.</P><P>Tenaiya Soulscorcher</font></td>
      </tr>
